      "created_at": "2023-08-28T10:08:27.969Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Hi!</p>\n<p>Would be great to have the possibility to scale the trainer power as it will almost certainly be different from that of a pedal or crank based power meter.</p>\n<p>The available power match feature is great but for example I have Garmin rally pedals that I don\u2019t want to keep on the bike I use with the trainer and rather leave them on another bike I use outdoors without needing to mount/unmount pedals each time I want to use the trainer.</p>\n<p>In my specific case I observe a 5/7% difference between the trainer and pedals power which is not so surprising and would be great to be able to scale this so that I don\u2019t have to keep the power meter pedals on the bike I use on the trainer all the time.</p>\n<p>I currently take this into account by correcting manually the power in my workouts but this sometimes messes up my recorded time in the different training zones.</p>",
